const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the Autonomous SmartDesk 2 worth it?', a: 'Yes, if your budget tops out at $350 and you want a motorized standing desk with memory presets. The SmartDesk 2 delivers a 60 by 30 inch desktop, 4 height presets, and a 270 lb lift capacity for $299. It is not as stable or as fast as the Uplift V2 or FlexiSpot E7, but it costs $100 to $200 less. If you can stretch your budget, those desks are better — but the SmartDesk 2 is the best value under $350.' },
  { q: 'How much does the Autonomous SmartDesk 2 wobble?', a: 'At seated height (under 38 inches), wobble is minimal and barely noticeable during typing. At full standing height (45 to 47 inches) with a heavy monitor arm, the steel legs flex noticeably and the desk sways when you type firmly. We measured about 4 millimeters of side-to-side movement at the desktop edge at full height. Dual-motor desks like the Uplift V2 show under 1 millimeter under the same load.' },
  { q: 'How long does assembly take for the SmartDesk 2?', a: 'Plan for about 90 minutes from box to finished desk. The frame bolts together in 30 minutes, the desktop attaches in 20 minutes, and the keypad and motor wiring take another 20 minutes. You need a second person to lift the desktop onto the frame — it weighs 40 to 55 pounds depending on the material. Autonomous includes an Allen key and a wrench; a cordless drill with a hex bit cuts about 15 minutes off the build.' },
